title: District volleyball finals set
text:
District volleyball finals set Brian McCallum , FLORIDA TODAY 8:16 p.m. EDT October 21, 2015 Holy Trinity’s Lara Boos taps the ball over the block of West Shore players Megan Green (16) and Kathryn Etherton this season. The teams will meet Thursday in a district final. (Photo: Craig Bailey/FLORIDA TODAY) 
Merritt Island High’s volleyball team, which has played in three of the last four Class 5A final fours, will take the next step toward returning via the District 14-5A championship on Thursday. 
The Mustangs will host Rockledge at 7 p.m. Both teams won semifinal matches on Tuesday. 
In Melbourne, Holy Trinity will face West Shore, also at 7, in the District 7-4A final at Melbourne Central Catholic. Merritt Island Christian will take on District 11-2A host Pine School on Friday in Hobe Sound. VIDEO: District 14-5A volleyball 
Fall high school sports postseason events will continue Friday and Saturday with district competitions in swimming and diving as well as cross country. 
Most Brevard County schools will compete in district meets on Friday at Indian River State College in Ft. Pierce: Class 2A schools at 9 a.m. and 1A schools 2 p.m. District meets for 3A schools will be next week. 
Because the top two teams from each district qualify for the regional playoffs, all district finalists are bound for the tournament that begins next week. 
Skateboarders win invitational event 
Three Brevard high school students were members of a team from Graffiti Skate Zone in Palm Bay that won the 23-team New England Am this month in Taunton, Mass. 
Max Potter of Cocoa Beach Jr./Sr. High along with Adam Tyler and Meagan Guy of Palm Bay made up three-quarters of the first-place team in the open age competition that included teams from across the U.S. 
Foot Locker scholarships open to senior athletes 
High school athletes planning to enter college in the fall of 2016 are invited to apply for one of 20 scholarships worth $20,000 to be awarded during this academic year. 
Applicants must be an active participant in a sports-related activity, going to college next fall and maintaining a 3.0 unweighted grade point average. Students can apply themselves or be nominated by someone at footlockerscholarathletes.com. The deadline is Dec. 17 at 5 p.m.
